This directory contains several examples that demonstrate the access to MCI layer in Libera instrument on platform B (Brilliance+, Single Pass E/H, Hadron).

To build all examples at once, simply type 'make' from the command line:

    libera@libera-dev:~/mci_tutorial$ cd ~/mci_tutorial
    libera@libera-dev:~/mci_tutorial$ make

This will build binaries in each directory. The 'Makefile' lists the subdirectories (SUBDIRS) in a sequence that is sorted by the difficulty starting from simplest to more demanding examples.

Edit 'Makefile.names' to set the version of Libera BASE that is installed in the OS. Default in this image is 2.8.
Do not edit 'Makefile.rules'

'common.h' contains definition of example nodes. These nodes can be modified to access other parameters and signals. They serve as examples only.

When adding other parameter nodes or signals, make sure to set the correct format (UInt32, Int16, etc.). Proper type can be retrieved while connected to Libera Brilliance+ and checking the type of selected node. See 2 examples (check 'components_type' and 'Value type' lines):

    root@libera:~# libera-ireg dump boards.raf3.signals.fa
    access_type=Stream
    atom_size=64
    group_size=1024
    components_names=[Va,Vb,Vc,Vd,Sum,Q,X,Y,LMT_l,LMT_h,r1,r2,r3,r4,r5,status]
    components_number=16
    components_type=int32

    root@james:~# libera-ireg info boards.raf3.conditioning.tuning.agc.power_level
    ---------------------------------------------------
      Registry hostname    : cache
      Node name            : power_level
      Value                : -65
      Value type           : Long ()
      Validator expression : [-80, 0]
      Num of values        : 1
      Full path            : boards.raf3.conditioning.tuning.agc.power_level
      Num of children      : 0
      Flags                : readable writable persistent
      Root                 : false
      Parent node name     : agc
      Children             : No children for this node
    ---------------------------------------------------


